Depending on the type of climate in your region, you might be limited in where you can plant boxwood. If you live in a colder area, boxwood should be planted in a location where it will receive full sunlight. Also consider positioning the plant where it will be protected from cold wind. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d4/Plant-Boxwood-Step-3Bullet1-Version-2.jpg/v4-460px-Plant-Boxwood-Step-3Bullet1-Version-2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d4/Plant-Boxwood-Step-3Bullet1-Version-2.jpg/v4-760px-Plant-Boxwood-Step-3Bullet1-Version-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
