In warmer areas, boxwood should be planted where it will receive partial shade. In all regions, boxwood should be planted exposed to the north or south. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c9/Plant-Boxwood-Step-3Bullet2-Version-2.jpg/v4-460px-Plant-Boxwood-Step-3Bullet2-Version-2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c9/Plant-Boxwood-Step-3Bullet2-Version-2.jpg/v4-760px-Plant-Boxwood-Step-3Bullet2-Version-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
